Apr 24 2009 	Great location indifferent service overall not bad for the price	stayed for a week with my family. Since I was forewarned about the noise from the disco, I asked specifically for a room on the higher floors and facing away from the main street. I got a room at the end of the 7th floor. I am glad to say that the room was very quiet with absolutely no disturbance of any kind. The housekeeping was unobtrusive and competent. I was somewhat stuck by the indifferent attitude of the girls in the reception. While not being rude, they were certainly not warm or friendly and did not seem to offer much assistance. In fact on most questions, they seemed ignorant.The rooms themselves were clean, the water pressure good and the bed comfy. My only grouse was that inspite of the individual AC controls in the room, the aircon seemed to have a mind of its own. It was freezing during the afternoons and strangely warm during the nights. I had to manually crank up the aircon in the middle of the night.The breakfast was unremarkable and par for a hotel of this class. The best part of the hotel was its location, very much in the heart of Bur Dubai and walking distance from the abra station from where you can cross over to Deira and the souks. Plenty of inexpensive eateries including indian vegetarian restaurants within walking distance.Overall I would definitely go back here. I paid an average of 100 USD per night which was pretty decent all things compared. Wish they had shuttle services to the malls which was missed, as well as complimentary pickup/drop to the airport.	
